Exceptions


Kafka clients are often used in Java/Spring Boot projects.

âœ” 2. Spring Boot Basics (Optional but Helpful)
Kafka integrates heavily with Spring Boot.
You should know:


REST API


Configurations


Dependency injection



âœ” 3. Linux & Command Line Basics
Kafka runs on Linux servers, so understand:


cd, ls, vim


Starting background processes


Exporting environment variables



âœ” 4. Basic Networking Concepts
Kafka is a distributed system. Know:


Ports


DNS/Hosts


Brokers (servers)


Clusters



âœ” 5. Zookeeper (Old) or KRaft (New)


Old Kafka uses Zookeeper.


New Kafka versions use KRaft (built-in).


Just have awareness; not deep knowledge needed initially.

